# Real email verification via EmailJS (https://www.emailjs.com)
# 1. Sign up for a free EmailJS account.
# 2. Create an email service (Gmail, Outlook, custom SMTP, etc) -> copy the Service ID.
# 3. Create a template that includes these variables:
#       to_email, to_name, verification_code, app_name
#    Use {{verification_code}} inside the template body.
# 4. Copy the Public Key from the Account tab.
# 5. Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values below.
# 6. Restart `npm start`.
#
# If these are unset, Strove falls back to displaying the code on screen for demo.

REACT_APP_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=
REACT_APP_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=
